author: @Opifex_
text: I don't get why finding the highest/lowest value is that hard? It's something very common in programming, no? Just start off by defining your max lower than all expected values, and your minimum higher than the expected values. Then iterate through all elements. If an element is higher than the current maximum, replace the value in max with the value you found. Do the opposite with the minimum:  replace the value if the value in the list is smaller than the currect minimum value.
